io.hekate.codec.fst

Class FstCodecFactory<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.hekate.codec.fst.FstCodecFactory<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - Base type of data that should be supported by this factory.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    CodecFactory<T>

    public class FstCodecFactory<T>
extends Object
implements CodecFactory<T>
    « start hereFST -based implementation of CodecFactory interface.

    Module dependency

    FST integration requires 'de.ruedigermoeller:fst' to be on the project's classpath.

    Configuration

    Each call of createCodec() method will produces a new independent FSTCoder instance and will configure it according to properties of this factory (see description of property setters). 

    
// Prepare FST codec factory.
FstCodecFactory<Object> fstCodec = new FstCodecFactory<>()
    .withUseUnsafe(true)
    // Register known types.
    .withKnownType(10001, MyClass1.class)
    .withKnownType(10002, MyClass2.class);

// Register FST codec factory and start a new node.
Hekate node = new HekateBootstrap()
    .withDefaultCodec(fstCodec)
    // ...other options...
    .join();

    See Also:
    HekateBootstrap.setDefaultCodec(CodecFactory)

      • setUseUnsafe

        public void setUseUnsafe(boolean useUnsafe)
        Sets the flag that indicates which implementation of FSTCoder should be used.

        If true then OnHeapCoder will be used. If false then DefaultCoder will be used.

        Default value of this parameter is true.

        Parameters:
        useUnsafe - Flag that indicates which implementation of FSTCoder should be used.
